eck for the presence of \\\"findElements\\\" rather than \\\"getBoundingClientRect\\\" directly. \\n\\nThe goal should be to cover behavior rather than source content. I wonder if checking just the wrapper's structure might provide better validity for resource loading without being too strict in expectations.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Inspecting function formats**\\n\\nI'm considering how to check for function beginnings. If `rawFunction` starts with \\\"function\\\", then using `startsWith` works perfectly. However, if it begins with \\\"/* ...\\\", that approach won't work at all. \\n\\nI might need to inspect the source more closely to understand the format. This could help me determine how to handle different function declarations properly. I really want to make sure I'm covering all possible cases efficiently!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_h4bf1aC0WArMwuvKy2f6IPto|fc_04279d04ba865cdd016a2582be60ac8190b0a5e85a3645fbec", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find /home/jovan/Work/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/org.seleniumhq.selenium/selenium-support/4.20.0 -maxdepth 3 -type f -printf '%p\\n' | head -100 && find /home/jovan/Work/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/org.seleniumhq.selenium/selenium-support/4.20.0 -type f | wc -l"}, "partialJson": "{\"command\":\"find /home/jovan/Work/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/org.seleniumhq.selenium/selenium-support/4.20.0 -maxdepth 3 -type f -printf '%p\\\\n' | head -100 && find /home/jovan/Work/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/org.seleniumhq.selenium/selenium-support/4.20.0 -type f | wc -l\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 673, "output": 634, "cacheRead": 31232, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 32539, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReaso